This paper deals with the problem of decentralized learning using ADMM, which is a popular optimization algorithm in machine learning. The paper focuses on the issue of unreliable agents in the system, which can be caused by noise, faults, and attacks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a robust variant of ADMM, which involves designing a network to achieve faster convergence, and provides conditions for exact convergence to the optimal solution. These aspects suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
